11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – Economic Development
14 SUBTITLE 4E. MARYLAND GROWTH INITIATIVE.
15 10–4E–01.
16 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
17 INDICATED.
18 (B) “CORPORATION” MEANS THE MARYLAND TECHNOLOGY
19 DEVELOPMENT CORPORATION.
20 (C) “FUND” MEANS THE MARYLAND GROWTH INITIATIVE FUND.
21 (D) “INITIATIVE” MEANS THE MARYLAND GROWTH INITIATIVE.
22 10–4E–02.
23 (A) THERE IS A MARYLAND GROWTH INITIATIVE IN THE CORPORATION.
24 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE INITIATIVE IS TO SUPPORT THE GROWTH OF
25 START–UP COMPANIES IN THE STATE BY:
26 (1) IDENTIFYING PROMISING COMPANIES IN THE PHASE BETWEEN
27 EARLY START–UP DEVELOPMENT AND SCALING;
28 (2) PROVIDING ACCESS TO EXPERTS IN REGULATORY PROCESSES,
29 MANUFACTURING, CLINICAL TRIALS, MARKET LAUNCHES, AND OTHER AREAS OF
30 BUSINESS;

SENATE BILL 763 3
1 (3) FACILITATING PRIVATE INVESTMENT IN COMPANIES;
2 (4) ASSISTING IN THE ACQUISITION OF INFRASTRUCTURE INCLUDING
3 OFFICE SPACE, EQUIPMENT, AND SUPPORT FOR PRODUCT DEVELOPMENT; AND
4 (5) PROVIDING TECHNICAL AND BUSINESS EXPERTISE.
5 10–4E–03.
6 (A) THERE IS A MARYLAND GROWTH INITIATIVE FUND.
7 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE FUND IS TO PROVIDE POSTSEED AND SERIES A
8 FUNDING TO QUALIFIED BUSINESSES IN THE STATE TO SCALE UP WITHOUT NEEDING
9 TO RELOCATE.
10 (C) THE CORPORATION SHALL ADMINISTER THE FUND.
11 (D) (1) THE FUND IS A SPECIAL, NONLAPSING FUND THAT IS NOT
12 SUBJECT TO § 7–302 OF THE STATE FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE.
13 (2) THE TREASURER SHALL HOLD THE FUND SEPARATELY, AND THE
14 COMPTROLLER SHALL ACCOUNT FOR THE FUND.
15 (E) THE FUND CONSISTS OF:
16 (1) MONEY APPROPRIATED IN THE STATE BUDGET TO THE FUND;
17 (2) PUBLIC AND PRIVATE INVESTMENT FUNDS;
18 (3) INTEREST EARNINGS; AND
19 (4) ANY OTHER MONEY FROM ANY OTHER SOURCE ACCEPTED FOR
20 THE BENEFIT OF THE FUND.
21 (F) THE FUND MAY BE USED ONLY:
22 (1) FOR THE PURPOSES DESCRIBED IN SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS
23 SECTION; AND
24 (2) TO PAY THE COSTS NECESSARY TO ADMINISTER THE INITIATIVE.
25 (G) (1) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL INVEST THE MONEY OF THE FUND
26 IN THE SAME MANNER AS OTHER STATE MONEY MAY BE INVESTED.

4 SENATE BILL 763
1 (2) ANY INVESTMENT EARNINGS OF THE FUND SHALL BE CREDITED
2 TO THE FUND.
3 (H) (1) THE GOVERNOR SHALL INCLUDE IN THE ANNUAL BUDGET BILL
4 AN APPROPRIATION OF $5,000,000 FOR THE INITIATIVE.
5 (2) THE FUNDING PROVIDED IN THIS SUBSECTION SHALL BE USED TO
6 SUPPLEMENT, NOT SUPPLANT, ANY FUNDS THAT WOULD OTHERWISE BE PROVIDED
7 TO THE INITIATIVE.
8 10–4E–04.
9 (A) THE INITIATIVE SHALL CREATE A CURATED LIST OF COMPANIES IN THE
10 STATE THAT ARE BETWEEN THE START–UP AND SCALING PHASES.
11 (B) PRIORITY SHALL BE GIVEN TO COMPANIES THAT ARE:
12 (1) CURRENT OR PRIOR RECIPIENTS OF FUNDING FROM THE
13 MARYLAND INNOVATION INITIATIVE;
14 (2) CURRENT OR PRIOR RECIPIENTS OF FUNDING FROM ANY OTHER
15 PROGRAM ADMINISTERED BY THE CORPORATION; AND
16 (3) MINORITY BUSINESS ENTERPRISES DESCRIBED IN § 9–4119(A) OF
17 THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE.
18 10–4E–05.
19 THE CORPORATION MAY ADOPT REGULATIONS TO IMPLEMENT THIS
20 SUBTITLE.
21 Article – State Finance and Procurement
22 6–226.
23 (a) (2) (i) This paragraph does not apply in fiscal years 2024 through 2028.
24 (ii) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, and unless
25 inconsistent with a federal law, grant agreement, or other federal requirement or with the
26 terms of a gift or settlement agreement, net interest on all State money allocated by the
27 State Treasurer under this section to special funds or accounts, and otherwise entitled to
28 receive interest earnings, as accounted for by the Comptroller, shall accrue to the General
29 Fund of the State.

SENATE BILL 763 5
1 (iii) The provisions of subparagraph (ii) of this paragraph do not
2 apply to the following funds:
3 212. the Department of Social and Economic Mobility Special
4 Fund; [and]
5 213. the Population Health Improvement Fund; AND
6 214. THE MARYLAND GROWTH INITIATIVE FUND.
7 Article – State Government
8 9–4119.
9 (a) This section applies to the following minority business enterprises:
10 (1) a publicly owned business if 1 or more minority persons own at least
11 51% of the stock of the business; or
12 (2) any other business if 1 or more minority persons own at least 50% of
13 the business.
14 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
15 October 1, 2026.

